fer to the flower as a symbol of the Virgin Mary, but it seems more likely that it also has a Germanic origin, probably as a short form of various girls' names based on <i>hros</i> ‘horse’ or <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’. The Latinate form <i>Rohesia</i> is commonly found in documents of the Middle Ages. As well as being a name in its own right, it is currently used as a short form of   Rosemary   and, less often (because of their different pronunciation), of other names beginning <i>Ros-</i>, such as   Rosalind   and   Rosamund ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Rose Brace was born about 1425, in Hanbury, Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom, her father, William Brace, was 26 and her mother, Mrs. William Brace, was 24. She married John More about 1449. They were the parents of at least 2 sons."},"et":{"Abt 1425–":"umbes 1425–Surnud","1425–Female":"1425–Surnud","1420–Male":"1420–Surnud","1438–1520":"1438–1520","1448–Male":"1448–Surnud","1400–Male":"1400–Surnud","1402–Female":"1402–Surnud","1448":"1448","1425":"1425","1402":"1402","about 1448":"umbes 1448","1400":"1400","about 1449":"umbes 1449","1520":"1520","about 1424":"umbes 1424","1420":"1420","Abt 1425":"umbes 1425","1438":"1438","England":"England","Benenden, Kent, England":"Benenden, Kent, England","Hanbury, Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Hanbury, Worcestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1425–":"noin 1425–Kuollut","1425–Female":"1425–Kuollut","1420–Male":"1420–Kuollut","1438–1520":"1438–1520","1448–Male":"1448–Kuollut","1400–Male":"1400–Kuollut","1402–Female":"1402–Kuollut","1448":"1448","1425":"1425","1402":"1402","about 1448":"noin 1448","1400":"1400","about 1449":"noin 1449","1520":"1520","about 1424":"noin 1424","1420":"1420","Abt 1425":"noin 1425","1438":"1438","England":"England","Benenden, Kent, England":"Benenden, Kent, England","Hanbury, Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Hanbury, Worcestershire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1425–":"environ 1425–Décédé